The Department of Trade and Industry said it would, in partnership with the Department of Small Business Development, the Eastern Cape provincial government and Buffalo City municipality, host a two-day empowerment summit It said the 19-20 July summit would also create a platform for all three spheres of government and the presidential BEE advisory council to enter into dialogue with the private sector and the general public. “These engagements and discussions will be critical in ensuring that an all-inclusive society that is economically developed and sustainable is achieved,” Trade and Industry Minister Rob Davies said. READ MORE: SA vows to protect sugar industry from cheaper imports The government has highlighted the need to encourage entrepreneurship to help create jobs in a country grappling with unemployment of around 27% of the labour force. – African News Agency